results.name: Number of benzenoids with 21 hexagons, C_(2h) symmetry and containing 2n carbon atoms.
comment: See Table 4 column 6 of Brinkmann et al. paper.
reference: G. Brinkmann, G. Caporossi and P. Hansen, "A survey and new results on computer enumeration of polyhex and fusene hydrocarbons", J. Chem. Inf. Comput. Sci., vol. 43 (2003), pp. 842-851.
example: If n=30 then the number of benzenoids with 21 hexagons with C_(2h) symmetry is 1 which is the first term in the sequence.
results.author: _Parthasarathy Nambi_, Sep 10 2006
